<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 9:42AM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern St.
Clair County through 1015 AM CDT...
At 942 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Appleton City, or 16 miles east of Butler, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Appleton City...                  Lowry City...
Johnson City...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
